entry.title: Flood Warning issued October 22 at 9:59AM EDT by NWS Melbourne FL
entry.summary:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida...
St Johns River Near Astor affecting Lake and Volusia Counties.
.The St Johns River at Astor is near 3 feet this morning, or very close to Moderate Flood Stage, due to past rainfall and downstream impacts from tides and surge. The river is forecast to slowly fall through late week. However, tide and wind effects could periodically slow the decline, especially later this week as northeasterly winds increase again.
For the St. Johns River...including Astor...Minor flooding is forecast.
Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.
The next statement will be issued 11 PM EDT.late tonight at 100 AM EDT.
* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.
* WHERE...St Johns River near Astor.
* WHEN...Until further notice.
* IMPACTS...At 3.0 feet, Water approaches or may enter lowest homes on or near Wildhog Road and nearby canals. Flooding reaches the parking lot of the Juno Trail Apartments. Flooding on portions of Alligator Road and Holiday Road. Lowest lying yards along Blue Creek are flooded. Roads at Astor Landing Campground and Lake Dexter Boat Ramp begin to flood. Water enters lower homes closest to the river on McPherson Lane.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:30 AM EDT Wednesday the stage was 3.0 feet. - Bankfull stage is 2.0 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 9:30 AM EDT Wednesday was 3.0 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to slowly fall from 3.0 this morning to 2.8 ft by Friday and over the upcoming weekend. - Flood stage is 2.3 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
entry.cap:areaDesc: Lake, FL; Volusia, FL

cap:parameter.value: FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE
